Anthony P. Bihl III
Chief Executive Officer



Experience
With more than 30 years of leadership experience in the medical device and diagnostics industries, Bihl is known for building high-performing teams, driving operational improvements and achieving exceptional financial results. Prior to joining Bioventus in December 2013, Bihl served as CEO and President of American Medical Systems, where he managed its restructuring following a series of acquisitions and led its eventual sale to Endo Pharmaceuticals. Before AMS, he was CEO of Siemens Medical Solutions Diagnostics, where he integrated two business units to form the division while achieving sales growth faster than market growth and exceeding profit targets. He also has served as President of the diagnostics division of Bayer Healthcare LLC, and held management positions at Sterling Diagnostic Imaging and E.I. DuPont. Bihl currently holds Board seats and provides strategic leadership for Greatbatch Inc., Spectral Diagnostics Inc., as well as the Bioventus Board of Managers.
Education
Bihl received his Bachelor of Science with distinction degree from Pennsylvania State University.
 




