Anthony P. Bihl IIIChief Executive Officer and Director, Bioventus Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships61$1,292,383As of Fiscal Year 2015
Background

		Mr. Anthony P. Bihl, III, also known as Tony, has been the Chief Executive Officer of Bioventus LLC since December 2, 2013 and Bioventus Inc. Mr. Bihl served as Head of The Endo Devices Operating Company at Endo Pharmaceuticals Holdings Inc. until July 2012. He joined Endo as Group President in June 2011 at acquisition of AMS. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at American Medical Systems Holdings Inc. since April 30, 2008. He served as the Chief ... Executive Officer and President of American Medical Systems Inc. since April 2008. He served as an Executive Vice President of Bayer HealthCare LLC and President of Bayer Diagnostics Division of Bayer Corporation. He served in senior leadership roles at Bayer Healthcare Diagnostics from 2000 to 2006. Prior to AMS, he served as the Chief Executive Officer of Siemens Medical Solutions Diagnostics Division from January 2007 to November 2007. Mr. Bihl served as the President of the Diagnostics Division of Bayer HealthCare AG from May 18, 2005 to 2006. He served as an Acting Head of Diagnostics Division and Senior Vice President of Business Planning & Administration for Bayer HealthCare LLC at Bayer Corporation. He joined Bayer's Diagnostics Division in January 2000 and served as its Vice President of Finance & Controlling for the Laboratory Testing Segment. Since 2002, he served as Senior Vice President of Business Planning & Administration (BPA) of Bayer HealthCare AG. He has 25 years of experience in financial, operational, global management, medical diagnostics, diagnostic imaging and biotechnology field. He held leadership roles in the HealthCare and Electronic Imaging businesses across Finance and Operations at Dupont. Mr. Bihl spent three years and served as Plant Manager of Medical Instrument Manufacturing. In a spin off from E.I. Dupont, he spent three years at Sterling Diagnostic Imaging where he served as Vice President Instrument Manufacturing and Service and Corporate Officer. He serves as the Chairman of the Board at Spectral Medical Inc. He has been a Director of Adnavance Technologies, Inc. since February 2008, Spectral Medical Inc. since March 2008 and American Medical Systems Holdings Inc. since April 2008. He serves as a Member of Board of Managers at Bioventus LLC, Bioventus Inc. He has been a Director of Nuvectra Corporation since March 2016. He served as a Director of Greatbatch, Inc. from October 13, 2011 to March 1, 2016. Mr. Bihl received his BS in Business Administration from Pennsylvania State University in 1978.Read Full Background




